itemDescription: English rugby union, rugby league and association footballer (1945-2008)

wikipedia_page.main: Michael "Mike" Seatter (born Jerrey Michael Henry Falvey) (4 September 1945 – 5 December 2008) was a rugby union, and professional association football (soccer), and rugby league footballer who played in the 1960s and 1970s. He played club level rugby union (RU) for Llandaff RFC, representative level association football for Jersey, and at club level for Barry Town F.C. and Magpies (Jersey), as a winger, and club level rugby league (RL) for Wakefield Trinity (Heritage No. 737), as a wing, i.e. number 2 or 5,
